Please give me some time to review it.

Sure, take the time you need.

honggfuzz -E HFND_DEST_ADDR=unix://...

If I may add my CHF 0.05: The weak-linked function working with struct sockaddr_* allows fuzzing via all compatible address families without requiring modifications in the fuzzer and there's no need for a parser. Relying on external environment variables makes it impossible for the fuzzer to specify the path (which may not be known until the program is started, see commit bfed5ea).
If the growing number of weak-linked functions is a concern another option could be to switch to a configuration structure. Pseudo code for a fuzzer:
int HonggfuzzNetDriverConfig(struct honggfuzz_netdriver_config *cfg) {
  static char *tmpdir = "/foo/bar";

  cfg->size = sizeof(*cfg);
  cfg->tmpdir = tmpdir;
  cfg->other_option = 1;

  struct sockaddr_un* addr = (struct sockaddr_un*)cfg->target_address;
  addr->sun_family = AF_UNIX;
  addr->sun_path = "‚Ä¶";
}
Binary compatibility is a bigger concern with this variant, hence setting the size to allow libhfnetdriver to work with older/smaller versions of the structure.

